VI'm reminded of that every time I walk past Highbury Fields
p10
aVin north London.
p11
aVIt's absolutely beautiful.
p12
aVThere's a big open green space.
p13
aVThere's Georgian buildings around the side.
p14
aVBut then there's this mud trap that cuts across the middle.
p15
aVPeople clearly don't want to walk all the way around the edge.
p16
aVInstead, they want to take the shortcut,
p17
aVand that shortcut is self-reinforcing.
